==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{chiefly|British}} A [[pave]]d footpath at the side of a [[road]].
# {{US}} Any paved [[exterior]] surface, as with a road or [[sidewalk]].
# The interior [[flooring]], especially when of stone, of large buildings such as a [[cathedral]].
# The [[material]] with which a surface is paved.
#* '''2001''', Michael Elliott, "[http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1101010730-168470,00.html Death In Genoa]," ''Time'', 22 July:
#*: [P]rotesters hurled Molotov cocktails and chunks of '''pavement''' into the faces of Czech police officers.

